loud.name: Ehrlund Microphones EHR-D Directional Condenser Microphone
loud.description: “Our most robust microphone. Designed specifically to block out unwanted sounds from sides and back, the EHR-D is a microphone designed for loud sound sources, tentatively for drums, horns and guitars. The housing is made for the rough life of being on the road.” Great for isolating an acoustic guitar when recording vocals at same time.

famous.name: Famous FS-1 Soprano Ukulele OBO
famous.description: Pretty little soprano, nice build with super-thin mahogany laminate, but with a sound that will rival most solid-wood ukes. Extremely light, with excellent projection and beautiful resonance. The Famous FS-1 is a Japanese build, identical to the Kiwaya KS-1, but sold only to the Japanese market. This older uke has a Rosewood fingerboard, which you won't find in production any longer...the newer ones are walnut.  Subtle striping at the soundhole is nice touch. Low action and great intonation, it's got a classic ukulele sound. Friction tuners. Tiny scratch on the headstock, mark on the first fret - see the photos for detail.Reasonable offers are welcome.

famous.name: 1895 Chickering Upright Piano
famous.description: 1895 Chickering Upright Piano.Been with our family for over 65 years.Very good shape.Year:	1895-1900Model: UprightHeight:	52Finish:	PolishedColor/Wood:	CherryPlate in excellent shape.The case: very good shapeNeeds tuning.Buyer responsible for delivery.A beautiful craftsman-style designed upright piano. A rare find and one of the most unique Chickering pianos. Chickering enjoys iconic status as the first piano manufacturer in America. The sprawling Chickering factory in Boston, was, at the time, a temple of innovation where piano design was constantly improving and evolving. Famous artists of the day such as Listz and Gottschalk endorsed the Chickering.This piano will meet the needs of any aspiring player. Its unique design also makes it a collector’s item and an instrument to be enjoyed for decades to come.

famous.name: Yamaha PM1000 Discrete 16 channel mixer frame, 6 channels + new parts
famous.description: Fully discrete these are famous for their thick and rich tone... great as mic preamps or as a summing unit or as an analog mixer. You just can't get a transformer loaded discrete channel with preamp, line amp, sends and EQ for anywhere near this price.Comes with enough new parts to recap a few channels and you can add more channel strips later if you need more.... they come up on ebay every few weeks or so.The 6 individual strips alone often sell for about 125-150 each plus tax and shipping.  The GA80080 Tamura Output Transformers sell for about 60-65 each.
